article.headline: Howard 75, Navy 65
article.story: WASHINGTON (AP) -- Jeron Smith scored 16 points and had a crucial 3-point play in the final 30 seconds to help Howard beat Navy 75-65 Tuesday night. It was the first win ever for Howard (3-4) against Navy (2-6). The Midshipmen had won in each of the past two seasons, their only previous meetings. Randy Hampton also scored 16, Eugene Myatt scored 15, and Curtis White and Kandi Mukole each had 10 for the Bison. Navy was led by Greg Sprink, who scored 16 of his 18 points in the second half. Adam Teague had 16 points. The game was tied 61-61 with two minutes left, but the Bison opened a 6-point lead before a 3-pointer by Teague cut it to 68-65 with 40 seconds left. Navy's Mark Veazey then stole the ball and fed it to Kaleo Kina, whose 3-point attempt for the tie rimmed out. Smith then converted a 3-point play when he was fouled on a quick charge up the court six seconds later, making the score 71-65. Mukole hit four free throws in the final seconds to put the game away. Howard stole the ball 10 times as part of Navy's 20 turnovers. The Bison also blocked eight shots.
